Subject: Linux-RT 2.6.27-RT
From: http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/projects/rt/
Acked-by: Sven-Thorsten Dietrich <sdietrich@suse.de>
change spinlock to be raw spinlock when serializing prints from NMI

From: Clark Williams <williams@redhat.com>


---

 arch/x86/kernel/nmi.c |    2 +-

---
 arch/x86/kernel/nmi.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

Index: linux-2.6.26-RT/arch/x86/kernel/nmi.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.26-RT.orig/arch/x86/kernel/nmi.c
+++ linux-2.6.26-RT/arch/x86/kernel/nmi.c
@@ -467,7 +467,7 @@ nmi_watchdog_tick(struct pt_regs *regs,
 	}
 
 	if (cpu_isset(cpu, backtrace_mask)) {
-		static DEFINE_SPINLOCK(lock);	/* Serialise the printks */
+		static DEFINE_RAW_SPINLOCK(lock);	/* Serialise the printks */
 
 		spin_lock(&lock);
 		printk(KERN_WARNING "NMI backtrace for cpu %d\n", cpu);
